      "date": "2012-11-02 15:56:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nI was thinking that the unlock should happen right after fixup_tpobj to minimize the lock hold time, but the current location is probably ok. This would only make a difference if the target object itself was a multi-linked file and some other thread is waiting on accessing it when this one failed.\n\nThe only other minor improvement would be the first CERROR(\"tpobj is dead, this should not happen\") message is useless and vague. It would be an improvement to make this match the others, with the device name and the FID in the error message.",
